title: my most recent instagram post
body:
So I’ve mentioned my love for Scott, Parker, and Raquel (nothing to do with Red- but vital to this message) many times before. My last paragraph, on Scott, was more centered around just him being over all amazing in general but this one is more personal I guess? Anyways, these three people probably help me more than they realize or even intend too. They are all people with their own lives outside of their fans, and i’m sure that sometimes, they probably want a break from people. Yet, they still make time for us. Truthfully, i’ve only spoken to Raquel and Scott myself, but I am still counting Parker in this because even though he hasn’t really interacted with me that much, I can still see how much he cares about his fans.

Moving on to why these three mean so much to me though, is to do with my personal life. I’ve spent 15 years without anybody-besides my parents- who I could lean on and trust. People always either just ignored me, or pushed me aside when someone else came along. I never mattered to people. Hell, one of my grandparents and my cousins did the exact same thing. I was just the weird autistic kid to them.

I guess I had a friend when I was 6, but we kind of lost touch over the years after I moved and so we rarely talked until last year when she started going to my school. I also have friends now who trully care about me, but I still have trouble with trusting that it’ll continue. So the fact that Scott, Raquel, and Parker are willing to not only acknowledge us, but talk to us means that much more to me. If people who don’t really know us that well, are willing to be so compassionate about their fans. They are busy people, and they don’t even need to, they’d probably be liked either way just because of their talent, and what they are choosing to do with their lives.

That being said, everytime I get a notification from one of them it helps to make me feel better. When Parker followed me I was really upset, but just seeing that he followed me cheered me up. Whenever I see that he watched my stories or likes my posts? Immediate smile. Everytime Scott messages me, it makes me even happier. He’s an adult, yet he makes time for us minors instead of just ignoring us, and his words are also so kind and inspirational. Raquel? She likes every single comment on posts, and replies. The first time I talked to her, she was quick to point out that she felt like everyone mattered just as much as she did. Her talent really didn’t matter to her in the grand scheme of things, she views us as her equals.

They all have their own contributions to making me feel better about myself, and other people too, and I hope they understand just how much even the little things mean to us ❤️

it’s literally been in the works for two.months. and i haven’t been able to write for it but a *very* ugly rp helped me out a ton and ..it’s coming…it’s lowkey gonna be a little crackt but it has all the godtier ships, a lot of fun, and a little angst..

/get asked like ‘i want someone to ask Andi __’
